.TH "drm_atomic_bridge_chain_check" 9 "drm_atomic_bridge_chain_check" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_atomic_bridge_chain_check \- Do an atomic check on the bridge chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" drm_atomic_bridge_chain_check
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ","
.BI "struct drm_crtc_state *crtc_state "  ","
.BI "struct drm_connector_state *conn_state "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge control structure
.IP "crtc_state" 12
new CRTC state
.IP "conn_state" 12
new connector state
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
First trigger a bus format negotiation before calling
\fIdrm_bridge_funcs\fP.\fBatomic_check\fP (falls back on
\fIdrm_bridge_funcs\fP.\fBmode_fixup\fP) op for all the bridges in the encoder chain,
starting from the last bridge to the first. These are called before calling
\fIdrm_encoder_helper_funcs\fP.\fBatomic_check\fP
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, a negative error code on failure
